  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<strong>Bard - Masterpieces</strong><br/><br/><p>You control the wind by telling a tale demonstrating the hubris of mortals.</p><p>Prerequisite: Perform (act) or Perform (oratory) 10 ranks.</p><p>Cost: Feat or 4th-level bard spell known.</p><p>Effect: This short monologue tells the story of a village priest who thought to command the gods. This so annoyed the gods of the weather that they gave him exactly what he wished for, and the priest's long-winded sermons tore apart his temple and scattered his parishioners. When you complete the performance, you conjure a great wind as if you had cast control winds.</p><p>Use: 3 bardic performance rounds.</p><p>Action: 3 full rounds.</p>",
